properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 15 at 6:50PM PST until February 16 at 4:00AM PST by NWS Spokane WA
properties.description:
...MOUNTAIN SNOW THIS WEEKEND...

.A moist Pacific storm system will spread accumulating snow
tonight into Sunday across the higher terrain of southeast
Washington and portions of northern Idaho.

* WHAT...Snow for the Palouse along and east of Highway 195.
Additional snow accumulations of up to two inches.

* WHERE...Pullman, Oakesdale, and Uniontown.

* WHEN...Through 4 AM PST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Travel will likely be difficult.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Snow will continue this evening before
ending overnight.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 4 AM PST SUNDAY FOR THE PALOUSE ALONG AND EAST OF HIGHWAY 195
